The paper discusses privacy-preserving machine learning algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions differential privacy, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of regularized empirical risk minimization (ERM) and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the application of these techniques to logistic regression and support vector machines, which are common algorithms in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
